Package pathfinder

Class Reproduction

  • java.lang.Object
    • simulator.Event
      • pathfinder.Reproduction

  • public class Reproduction
extends Event
    This class extends Event, providing a specific implementation of Event.doEvent(): reproducing a certain Individual and adding the newborn to the list of alive Individuals.
    See Also:
    Event, Individual

      • Reproduction

        public Reproduction​(Individual i,
                    java.util.LinkedList<Individual> l,
                    Grid g,
                    double[] par,
                    double present)
        Constructor used during simulation, each time an existing individual reproduces.

        Reproduction time is generated according to simulator generator and parameters given.

        Parameters:
        i - individual to link this move event to.
        l - list of alive individuals.
        g - grid where individual will move.
        par - reproduction parameters to be used in generating event time.
        present - time to be added to generated time.

    • Method Detail

      • doEvent

        public java.util.List<Event> doEvent​()
        This method reproduces the individual.

        First, it sees the percentage of parent path that newborn will inherit. Then, it creates an Individual with that prefix, adds him to the alive individual list and generates death, first reproduction and movement of newborn. Also, generates next reproduction of parent.

        Specified by:
        doEvent in class Event
        Returns:
        next reproduction of existing Individual and the death, reproduction and move of newborn, if Event time is lower than individual death time and simulation final instant.
        See Also:
        Event.doEvent()
